# csplit

> Split a file into pieces
> This generates files named "xx00", "xx01", and so on
> More information: https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/csplit

- Split a file at lines 5 and 23:

`csplit {file value} {int value: 5} {int value: 23}`

- Split a file every 5 lines (this will fail if the total number of lines is not divisible by 5):

`csplit {file value} {int value: 5} {*}`

- Split a file every 5 lines, ignoring exact-division error:

`csplit -k {file value} {int value: 5} {*}`

- Split a file at line 5 and use a custom prefix for the output files:

`csplit {file value} {int value: 5} -f {string value: prefix}`

- Split a file at a line matching a regular expression:

`csplit {file value} /{string value: regular_expression}/`
